<p><b>Additional notes on "Freebie" Quests:</b></p>

<ul>
<li>Just hail the NPC and follow the dialog and they will hand you the items you need to combine and return to the same NPC.
<li>You can get skilled up to 54 using these methods for basically free.
<li>There are 4 levels of skills you have to do for each trade.
<li>Each level item has trivial at: 31, 38, 46 and 54.
<li>You have to do 100 combine per each level. You can only do this 20 at a time.
<li>When you turn in the items they must be UNSTACKED, i.e. 4 at a time.
<li>Level 3 and 4 for pottery requires two steps, wheel and kiln.
<li>You can fail these. I have failed couple of items in tailoring, at skill of 224 or 235 with Trophy.  However, if you fail 1 and only have combined 99 of items, NPC still gives you the next step after turning in 99 items, not 100. 
<li>When noting /loc, pay attention to the last digits, they represent the height. With multiple levels, it's difficult to locate the NPCs.
<li>Lastly, some of the NPCs seems to be bugged, especially baking one. If you find that after turning in 5 stacks (100 items) NPC gives you the 6th stack of the same, finish up that stack and turn them in. Then do the /hail again and follow the dialog again. This seems to reset and NPC gives you the next level items.
</ul></p><p>
